<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 24 at 2:55PM CDT  by NWS San Angelo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern
Sterling County through 330 PM CDT...
At 254 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles east of Garden City, moving east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Sterling City.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
